d 'EDITPROFILE': module to maintain profile.do settings
d
d	editprofile locates, opens, and optionally creates the
d user-specific profile.do file.    Stata executes profile.do
d automatically whenever it is launched, allowing users to set	 
d custom defaults (working directory, graphics scheme, memory
d allocation, extra ado    directories, etc.).	  Called without
d any options, editprofile opens the first profile.do found in
d Stata's    standard search order — the current working
d directory, the Stata installation directory,	  or the PERSONAL
d ado directory.  If no profile.do exists yet, an error message is
d shown    and the user is advised to use the create option. 
d
d KW: profile
d KW: file management
d
d Requires: Stata version 12
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260619
d
d Author: Wu LiangHai,  Anhui University of Technology
d Support: email agd2010@@yeah.net
d
f editprofile.ado
f editprofile.sthlp
f ../p/profile.do
